    <div class="auction-description">
      <h2>Skills</h2>
      Chai, Express, Mocha, Node.js, and Sails.js
      <p>Open Opportunities uses the open source <a href="http://sailsjs.org/">sails.js</a> MVC framework (Node.js / Express).  Currently, a task creator should receive the following notification if a task they created receives a comment. However, this functionality has broken, without breaking the build&#39;s test suite. This issue sees the creation of a failing test (or tests) that will only pass when the notification functionality is restored, along with the fix to make those tests pass.</p>

<h2>Auction rules</h2>

<p>Registered users on micropurchase.18f.gov may bid to deliver the requirements in this auction. The lowest bidder at the time the auction closes shall receive the award. The awarded bidder shall have five business days to deliver the requirements. Upon successful completion of the requirements, 18F shall pay the winning bidder.</p>

<p>Also see our <a href="https://micropurchase.18f.gov/faq">policies and guidelines page</a>.</p>

<h2>Acceptance criteria</h2>

<h3>1.) Conditions for the test to fail</h3>

<p>When the bug is present, and a user who is not the task creator comments on the task, and no email is generated, </p>

<p>Then test(s) written as part of this micro-purchase will fail.</p>

<p><hr /></p>

<h3>2.) Fixing the bug, making the failing tests pass</h3>

<p>Given the failing tests (defined above)</p>

<p>When the bug has been fixed,</p>

<p>And a task creator receives a notification when a task receives a comment,</p>

<p>Then test(s) written as part of this micro-purchase will pass.</p>

<h2>General acceptance criteria</h2>

<ul>
<li>All new functionality does not degrade code climate rating</li>
<li>The failing test(s) should be marked as pending (with xit) and all other tests should pass</li>
<li>Any additional tests will not interfere with existing tests.</li>
<li>New features do not degrade accessibility (use pa11y/HTML Code Sniffer).</li>
</ul>

<h2>Resources</h2>

<ul>
<li><a href="https://github.com/18F/openopps-platform">https://github.com/18F/openopps-platform</a></li>
</ul>

<h2>Deliverables</h2>

<p>A single pull request submitted to <a href="https://github.com/18F/openopps-platform">https://github.com/18F/openopps-platform</a> with clear, descriptive commits that satisfy all of the above acceptance criteria.</p>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>

